The novel features believed characteristic of the invention are set forth in the appended claims. The invention itself however, as well as a preferred mode of use, further objects and advantages thereof, will best be understood by reference to the following detailed description of an illustrative embodiment when read in conjunction with the accompanying drawings, wherein:


FIG. 1 depicts a cell cluster within a wireless communication system having a cellular architecture within which the method and system of the present invention may be implemented;


FIG. 2 is a partially schematic diagram depicting a mobile subscriber unit 210 transiting from cell 101 to cell 104;


FIG. 3 is a partially schematic representation demonstrating concepts involved in handoff based on a Received Signal Strength Indicator;


FIG. 4 illustrates events subsequent to handoff cell determination unit 322 initiating cell handoff request signal 324 as was discussed in relation to FIG. 3;


FIG. 5 depicts a partially schematic diagram of concepts involved when cell 104 handoff channel assignment unit 410 assigns an unused channel to mobile subscriber unit 210 in response to cell handoff request signal 324;


FIG. 6A is a high-level logic flowchart depicting the method and process of one illustrative embodiment of the present invention;


FIG. 6B is a high-level logic flowchart depicting the method and process of another illustrative embodiment of the present invention;


FIG. 7 depicts a pictorial representation of a data-processing system which can be utilized in accordance with the method and system of an illustrative embodiment of the present invention; and


FIG. 8 is an illustration of a representative hardware environment which can be utilized in accordance with the method and system of an illustrative embodiment of the present invention.
